tip, on number 11, sin is opp/hyp, cos is adj/hyp, and tan is sin/cos. You know sin is negative and so is tan. For tan to be negative, the denominator (cos) needs to be positive. Which leaves us with A, E, and D. We also know cos is adj/hyp. And from sin we're given that the hyp is 25. Thus the answer is D

Tip to save you questions on the easier algebra problems... it’s WAY easier to work backwards rather than the “traditional” way of doing algebra problems. For number one for example, 3x/4+5=11. Subtract 5 from 11 because you added it on the other side,and 11 becomes 6, multiply by 4 instead of divide and get 24, and divide by 3 instead of multiple to get 8. Just do the opposite of whatever the longer signs operation is (multiplication becomes division, addition becomes subtraction, etc.) to the other side. You can do it in your head that way.

This would only take about 10-15 seconds at most with a calculator, leaving you room to answer more questions.
